In [1]:
library(RCurl)
library(jsonlite)
station_link <- 'https://gbfs.citibikenyc.com/gbfs/en/station_status.json' 
apiOutput <- getURL(station_link)  
apiData <- fromJSON(apiOutput)  
stationStatus <- apiData$data$stations 
cols <- c('num_bikes_disabled','num_docks_disabled', 'station_id', 'num_ebikes_available', 'num_bikes_available', 'num_docks_available') 
stationStatus = stationStatus[,cols]

task 1

a data set showing the number of stations and bikes in those station

task 2

library(RCurl) library(jsonlite) these allow use of necessary packages station_link <- 'https://gbfs.citibikenyc.com/gbfs/en/station_status.json' makes a varriable that is the link apiOutput <- getURL(station_link)
gets information/results from that url and stores it in varriable apiData <- fromJSON(apiOutput) converts the results to a dataframe R stationStatus <- apiData$data$stations sets stationStatus to the data in stations cols <- c('num_bikes_disabled','num_docks_disabled', 'station_id', 'num_ebikes_available', 'num_bikes_available', 'num_docks_available') makes a vector called cols that has the names of some of the collumns in stations stationStatus = stationStatus[,cols] sets stationStatus to the collumns that were made in cols
